data.chText: （木、金属或塑料）钉子，楔子，橛子，短桩
data.enText: a short piece of wood, metal or plastic used for holding things together, hanging things on, marking a position, etc.

data.chText: 门边有个钩子可以挂衣服。
data.enText: There's a peg near the door to hang your coat on.
tent peg
a small pointed piece of wood or metal that you attach to the ropes of a tent and push into the ground in order to hold the tent in place
clothes peg
clothespin
a piece of wood or plastic used for attaching wet clothes to a clothes line
tuning peg
a wooden screw for making the strings of a musical instrument tighter or looser
off the peg
off the rack
made to a standard average size and not made especially to fit you
He buys his clothes off the peg.
off-the-peg fashions
bring/take sb down a peg (or two)

data.chText: 杀某人的威风；挫某人的锐气
data.enText: to make sb realize that they are not as good, important, etc. as they think they are
He needed to be taken down a peg or two.
a peg to hang sth on
something that gives you an excuse or opportunity to discuss or explain sth
a square peg (in a round hole)
a person who does not feel happy or comfortable in a particular situation, or who is not suitable for it

data.chText: 用夹子夹住；用楔子钉住
data.enText: to fasten sth with

data.chText: 他们的湿衣服都夹在外面的绳子上了。
data.enText: All their wet clothes were pegged out on the line.

data.chText: 她忙着用橛子把帐篷钉牢在地上。
data.enText: She was busy pegging her tent to the ground.

data.chText: 使工资、价格等固定于某水平（或与…挂钩）
data.enText: to fix or keep prices, wages, etc. at a particular level
Pay increases will be pegged at 5%.

data.chText: 分期付还贷款按你的收入计算。
data.enText: Loan repayments are pegged to your income.
to think of sb in a particular way

data.chText: 她觉得他是个大手大脚的人。
data.enText: She pegged him as a big spender.
be level pegging
having the same score

data.chText: 参赛选手在第3轮以后成绩不相上下。
data.enText: The contestants were level pegging after round 3.
peg away (at sth)

data.chText: 坚持不懈地工作（或努力）
data.enText: to continue working hard at sth or trying to achieve sth difficult
peg sb/sth↔back
to stop sb/sth from winning or increasing the amount by which they are ahead

data.chText: 每次我们得分，几分钟后便被追上。
data.enText: Each time we scored we were pegged back minutes later.
peg out
to die

tr: a wooden pin pushed or driven into a surface
a holder attached to the gunwale of a boat that holds the oar in place and acts as a fulcrum for rowing
regulator that can be turned to regulate the pitch of the strings of a stringed instrument
a prosthesis that replaces a missing leg

example: fever left him weak on his sticks

tr: small markers inserted into a surface to mark scores or define locations etc.
stabilize (the price of a commodity or an exchange rate) by legislation or market operations
example: The weak currency was pegged to the US Dollar

pierce with a wooden pin or knock or thrust a wooden pin into

value.def: A peg is a small hook or knob that is attached to a wall or door and is used for hanging things on.

example.ex: His work jacket hung on the peg in the kitchen.
example.tran: 他的工作服挂在厨房里的挂钩上。

value.def: A peg is a small device which you use to fasten clothes to a washing line.

value.boxr_value: in AM, usually use 美国英语通常用 clothespin

value.def: A peg is a small piece of wood or metal that is used for fastening something to something else.

example.ex: He builds furniture using wooden pegs instead of nails.
example.tran: 他用木楔子取代钉子制作家具。

example.ex: ...the noise of the hammer striking the steel pegs.

value.def: If you peg something somewhere or peg it down, you fix it there with pegs.

example.ex: ...trying to peg a double sheet on a washing line on a blustery day...
example.tran: 大风天试图用衣夹把双人床单固定在晾衣绳上

example.ex: Peg down netting over the top to keep out leaves.
example.tran: 用销钉在顶上加固防护网，防止叶子落入。

example.ex: ...a tent pegged to the ground nearby for the kids.
example.tran: 用楔子固定在附近地面上供孩子们用的帐篷

value.tran: 用销钉（或楔子、木栓）固定

value.def: If a price or amount of something is pegged at a particular level, it is fixed at that level.

example.ex: Its currency is pegged to the dollar...
UK trading profits were pegged at £40 million...
example.tran: 英国的贸易利润固定在4,000万英镑。

example.ex: The Bank wants to peg rates at 9%.
example.tran: 该银行想把利率限定在9%。

value.tran: 限定（价格、数量等）；把…固定在一定水平；使与…挂钩

value.def: If you say that someone should be brought down a peg or be taken down a peg, you mean that they should be made to realize that they are not so important or wonderful as they think they are.

example.ex: We thought it was time they were brought down a peg or two...
example.tran: 我们认为是时候煞煞他们的嚣张气焰了。

example.ex: We'd have liked to see her taken down a peg, but not this way.
example.tran: 我们乐意看到她杀威风，但不是用这种方法。

value.def: Off-the-peg clothes are made in large numbers and sent to shops, not made specially for a particular person.

example.ex: Instead of dining in top restaurants and wearing expensive suits, he likes to eat hamburgers and buys clothes off the peg.
example.tran: 比起穿着昂贵的套装到高档饭店吃饭，他更喜欢吃汉堡、买成衣。

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 off-the-rack

value.def: If you describe someone as a square peg in a round hole, you mean that they are in a situation or doing something that does not suit them at all.

example.ex: Taylor is clearly the wrong man for the job — a square peg in a round hole.
example.tran: 泰勒明显不适合做这项工作——简直就是方枘圆凿。
